{
  "texts": [
    "Therefore we believe that conducting the first survey of hallucinations in LLMs for causal discovery will be useful to researchers for optimal model selection in the field of causality.Given that hallucinations frequently stem from a lack of pre-trained data on a topic [13], we need options to augment the LLMs with newer or better data.",
    "The default option after pre-training the LLM on a vast corpus and billions of parameters is to fine-tune the LLM for specific purposes using relevant data.",
    "However, much like pre-training, fine-tuning can be computationally expensive.",
    "Moreover, the corpus needed to fine-tune the LLM may not always be available or accessible.",
    "One cheaper option is few-shot learning [1] where the LLM learns and generalizes from only a few training examples."
  ]
}